EUGENE, Oregon – Jamaican Shericka Jackson won her first-ever World title with a stunning victory in the women’s 200 meters at Hayward Field here late Thursday evening. The 28-year-old powered to a new meet record 21.45 seconds to become the second fastest woman ever and the fastest alive, as she dominated the final from start to finish. Fellow Jamaican Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce finished second in a season-best 21.81 while Great Britain’s Dina Asher-Smith copped bronze in 22.02. Olympic champion Elaine Thompson-Herah, also of Jamaica, finished one from last in 22.39. In the men’s final, Noah Lyles mounted a successful defense of his title in scintillating 19:31 seconds to lead an American sweep of the podium. Trinidadian Jereem Richards, the sole Caribbean presence in the field, finished sixth in 20.08.